          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/17562788-the-chronicle-of-sapta-sindhu">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer564371216" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5729411602577258368">It is one of the few books which delve deep into the historicity of not only India but the whole of central, west Asia. Wonderfully researched and written, the book tells us the tale of valor of the people of Sapta Sindhu/Indus valley and how they unite and fight against the Greek queen Kassnddra and her seven brothers. <br/>It is recommended for learning, fun and for a thrilling read.Go for it. If you have enjoyed Amish then take it as the fourth book in his trilogy!!...go on and read it. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


